data.name: Vegetarian Paneer Tikka Masala
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and flavorful paneer tikka masala bursting with spices, perfect for a comforting dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut paneer into cubes and marinate in yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, and spices for at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a pan and saut√© chopped onions until golden brown.
Add the marinated paneer and cook until slightly charred.
Stir in tomato puree and cook until the oil separates.
Add cream and simmer for a few minutes to thicken the sauce.
Garnish with cilantro and serve hot with naan or rice.
